impl Tool for BashTool {
    fn classify_summary(&self, args: &Value) -> String {
        let cmd = args.get("command")
            .and_then(|v| v.as_str())
            .unwrap_or("(unknown)");
        let preview: String = cmd.chars().take(60).collect();
        format!("bash: {preview}")
    }
}
```

The 80-char truncation prevents the TUI from breaking when models pass large JSON blobs as arguments. The `...` suffix signals to the user that content was clipped.

